core.comp3111

Class Environment

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.comp3111.Environment

  • public class Environment
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a centralized interface for accessing data tables and charts. It also provides save and load functions which serializes the EnvironmentParams class using a custom file extension ".comp3111"
    Author:
    kwaleung, kpor

      • operandsCompare

        public boolean operandsCompare(double value,
                               java.lang.String operator,
                               double threshold)
        This function reads an operator in String and translate it into real comparison operation and return the result in boolean.
        Parameters:
        value - value (Type: double) to be compared with the threshold
        operator - operand (">","<", ">=","<=", "==", "!=") to be used for comparison
        threshold - threshold (Type: double) to be use for compared
        Returns:
        boolean true if the operation of "value operator threshold" returns true, false otherwise

      • filterDatasetByNum

        public java.lang.String filterDatasetByNum(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                           java.lang.String colName,
                                           java.lang.String operator,
                                           double threshold,
                                           boolean isReplaced)
                                    throws DataTableException
        Return the name of a new DataTable.

        Replace/Create a data set by filtering numeric data of a column.

        Filter data using various comparison operators (">","<", ">=","<=", "==", "!=").

        Parameters:
        datasetName - name of the selected DataTable
        colName - name of the column being filtered
        operator - operator to be used for comparison
        threshold - value to be used for comparison
        isReplaced - set true to replace the selected DataTable with the filtered DataTable

        set false to create a new DataTable with the filtered rows

        Returns:
        String or null name of a new DataTable, "Empty DataTable" or null
        Throws:
        DataTableException - if operation on DataTable is invalid

      • randSplitDatasetByNum

        public java.lang.String[] randSplitDatasetByNum(java.lang.String datasetName,
                                                int splitRatio,
                                                boolean isReplaced)
                                         throws DataTableException
        Return an array of String of two split DataTable

        Randomly split a data set into 2 data sets by rows.

        Set the parameters, isReplaced, to replace the current data set OR to create new DataTable(s).

        After the split, both data sets should keep the same column names.

        Parameters:
        datasetName - name of the selected DataTable
        splitRatio - the percentage of split (0% to 100%)
        isReplaced - set true to replace the selected DataTable with one of the new DataTable

        set false to create a new DataTable with the filtered rows

        Returns:
        String[] or null First String in the array will be name of first new DataTable

        Second String in the array will be name of second new DataTable

        "" (Empty String) in the first/second index of array if the first/second new DataTable is empty

        Throws:
        DataTableException - if operation on DataTable is invalid
